title: Earthquake measuring 6.0 strikes northwest Argentina - International - World
text:
Related Moderate 5.4-magnitude earthquake rocks Tokyo Magnitude 4.0 earthquake jolts San Francisco Bay Area Three dead as 6.4 earthquake hits China's Xinjiang A magnitude 6.0 earthquake struck Argentina in the northwest corner of the country on Saturday, the US Geological Survey reported.
The USGS said the quake occurred 131 kilometres (81 miles) southeast of the provincial capital Salta.
